[38;2;255;255;255mâº[39m [1mTASK_COMPLETE[22m

  I successfully completed the task. Here is the full summary provided by
  GPT OSS 120B model after analyzing the project:

  [1mComplete Response from GPT OSS 120B:[22m

  [1mProject Overview â€“ terminalcp[22m

  terminalcp is a Node-JS library and MCP-compatible server that lets AI
  agents (or any program) control interactive command-line tools just like
  a human would. It provides a "Playwright-for-the-terminal" style API that
   can:

  â€¢ Spawn and manage any CLI process (debuggers, REPLs, build tools, etc.)
  in a pseudo-TTY.
  â€¢ Send keystrokes, special keys, and control sequences to those
  processes.
  â€¢ Read output either as a full rendered screen (for TUIs, debuggers,
  etc.) or as a raw stream (for logs, builds, etc.).
  â€¢ Run multiple sessions simultaneously, with each session persisting
  across client disconnects.
  â€¢ Allow users to attach to AI-spawned sessions from their own terminal
  (similar to screen/tmux), watch the AI's actions, or intervene.

  [1mKey Features[22m

  | Capability          | Description

                                            |
  |---------------------|--------------------------------------------------
  -------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ------------------------------------------|
  | Process control     | Start/stop processes, set working directory, give
   them a human-readable name.
                                            |
  | Input               | Send text, arrow keys, Ctrl-C, etc., using
  escape-sequence strings.
                                                  |
  | Output              | stdout â€“ full rendered screen (good for TUIs,
  debuggers). stream â€“ raw incremental output (good for logs).
                                               |
  | Session management  | List, stop individual or all sessions; sessions
  survive server restarts.
                                             |
  | MCP & CLI           | Exposes a single JSON-based tool (terminalcp) for
   MCP clients (VS Code, Claude, Cursor, etc.) and a standalone CLI
  (terminalcp start â€¦, terminalcp attach â€¦, etc.). |
  | Programmatic API    | TerminalManager class lets Node apps drive
  terminals programmatically (start, send input, get output, stop).
                                                  |
  | Attachable sessions | Users can attach to any running session from
  their own terminal (Ctrl-B to detach).
                                                |
  | Persistence         | Sessions run in a background server
  (~/.terminalcp/server.socket) and persist across client restarts.
                                                         |
  | Cross-platform      | Works on macOS, Linux, etc., with Node 20+.

                                            |

  [1mTypical Use Cases[22m

  â€¢ Debugging â€“ drive LLDB/GDB, Python pdb, etc., step-by-step.
  â€¢ AI-to-AI collaboration â€“ run Claude, Gemini, etc., as subprocesses.
  â€¢ REPL / shell automation â€“ drive Python, Node, Ruby REPLs.
  â€¢ TUI testing â€“ automate Vim, htop, or any curses-based UI.
  â€¢ Log monitoring â€“ stream build logs, server output, with incremental
  "since-last" reads.
  â€¢ User-agent collaboration â€“ AI spawns a process, user attaches to watch
  or help.

  [1mHow It Works (Layers)[22m

  1. TerminalManager â€“ core library using node-pty and headless xterm.js to
   emulate a terminal.
  2. TerminalServer â€“ background process managing all sessions via a
  Unix-domain socket.
  3. TerminalClient â€“ used by both the MCP server and CLI to talk to the
  server.
  4. User Interfaces â€“ MCP server (exposes terminalcp tool) and CLI
  (stand-alone commands).

  [1mInstallation & Quick Start[22m

  {
    [36m"mcpServers"[39m: {
      [36m"terminalcp"[39m: {
        [36m"command"[39m: [31m"npx"[39m,
        [36m"args"[39m: [[31m"@mariozechner/terminalcp@latest"[39m, [31m"--mcp"[39m]
      }
    }
  }

  Then use the MCP JSON commands (e.g.,
  {"action":"start","command":"python3 -i","name":"py-repl"}) or the CLI
  (terminalcp start my-app "npm run dev").

  [1mBottom line:[22m terminalcp gives AI agents (and developers) a robust,
  programmatic way to run, control, and monitor any interactive terminal
  program, with full PTY emulation, multi-session support, and both
  programmatic and CLI interfaces.

  The task was completed successfully - I was able to start opencode with
  the specified model, switch to GPT OSS 120B, and capture the complete
  analysis response from the model.
